    "title": "Marketing Data Connectors: A Unified Integration Architecture for Multi-Platform Attribution",
    "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18860349",
    "publication_date": "2026-03-04",
    "description": "Attribution models are only as good as their data \u2014 yet marketing data is fragmented across dozens of platforms with incompatible schemas, rate limits, and authentication models. This paper presents a unified connector architecture that normalizes data from Facebook Ads, Google Ads, TikTok, LinkedIn, Salesforce, and 40+ additional platforms into a canonical attribution event model. The framework includes OAuth2 authentication, intelligent rate limiting, schema validation, and incremental sync \u2014 providing the data infrastructure layer for Robinson (2026a) through (2026h).",
